      <acqinfo encodinganalog="541">
         <head>Acquisition Information</head>
         <p>The records of the French and American Claims Commission were purchased by the Library
            of Congress in 1931. The records were originally processed as part of the Manuscript
            Division's David Dixon Porter Papers from which they were separated. </p>
      </acqinfo>
